## THREAD 2: THE THREE-OPTION DISCLOSURE (I need help / I want to help / I want to make money)

**Source-verified Truth-Always finding: the user-intent three-option split as Founder describes it ("I need help / I want to help / I want to make money") does NOT exist anywhere in the current codebase.** No file in `LianaBanyanPlatform/src/` contains those strings. The librarian substrate has no canon, pearl, or scribe entry for it. This is spec only.

The codebase has TWO first-run components in `src/renderer/components/`:

**SaltFighterFirstRun.tsx** (gate `mnemosyne-saltfighter-done`). Old flow. Screen 1: star-field text crawl + "Do not show again" checkbox + Enter button. Screen 2: HEOHO 16-initiatives grid + "Join for $5/year" button. Screen 3: "Never Repeat Yourself" folder picker + benchmark nudge + "Open the app." **MnemosyneTabView only renders Bp067FirstRunSpine, not SaltFighterFirstRun. SaltFighter is dead code in the current flow.** The line 53 comment in MnemosyneTabView says "supersedes SaltFighterFirstRun + OnboardingWizard."

**Bp067FirstRunSpine.tsx** (the active flow per Thread 1 above). Its "three options" are the A/B/C technical fallback for AI-setup failure (bundled / borrow / folder), not a user-intent split.

What each existing A/B/C option does at level 2:
- A: Single action "Start bundled AI" → calls `setupPrivateAI`. Retry-err state shows "Try again."
- B: Single action "Request a frontier node" → calls `lbRequestFrontierBorrow`. Result card shows connected-node count or error.
- C: Single action "Browse for model folder" → opens folder dialog. **Path is stored in state only. No IPC call follows. Dead-end at level 2.**

Level 3 (only Option B has any): the borrow result card shows connected nodes or an error string. No further branch.

The 16 initiatives are hardcoded as a flat grid in `SaltFighterFirstRun.tsx` lines 17-34. **No mapping to user-intent axes.** Since the intent split does not exist, there is no implemented mapping from "I need help" / "I want to help" / "I want to make money" to specific initiatives.

The $5 join modal (FirstStepsView) terminates with `onClose()` and drops the user into the bare app. **No post-join routing.** The intent split was presumably meant to fill this gap.

